rows.label: qst103904_msg0001
rows.name:
What can I do you for?
After delivery, are you?

rows.label: qst103904_msg0002
rows.name:
Handling fees for Iyasaki
by way of Avaritia?

rows.label: qst103904_msg0003
rows.name:
Oh, you're talking about the delivery
from Rex! That lad sure does send
money home like a right good lad.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0004
rows.name:
Listen, we run an honest business.
We got nothing to hide.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0005
rows.name:
Port authority charges 3% to
load goods onto the ship.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0006
rows.name:
Then for large sums you pay another
2% for an escort. After that, it's another
2% to send it to Alba Margen.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0007
rows.name:
So if you started with 88,200G...
You're looking at 82,166G
heading for the capital.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0008
rows.name:
What are you sending it to
the capital for?

rows.label: qst103904_msg0009
rows.name:
There's no shipping lane
from Torigo to Liberalitas.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0010
rows.name:
There's not much that gets
sent to Liberalitas. Supply and
demand, boyo.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0011
rows.name:
I would go ask the Nopon
courier in Superbia about
his handling fees, if I were you.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0012
rows.name:
You'll probably find him loading
goods at Port Anangham.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0014
rows.name:
Everyone just calls him
"boss" so I forget.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0101
rows.name:
It would be a bit cheaper without
the port authority charges.

rows.label: qst103904_msg0102
rows.name:
But that money goes towards
wharf maintenance and hiring
supervisory staff. It's pretty vital.
